document_data.mainbody:
At some point in the 1350s [[DR]], [[Pasha]] [[Abon Duum]] of [[Manshaka]] had fortuitously been granted guardianship of the [[kittenlord]], heir to the power of the [[cat lord]], a minor power of felines. However, Duum desired to corrupt and dominate the child, and therefore made a deal with the mightier power Malar to keep the vengeful old [[Catlord (old)|Catlord]] off his back. Duum wished to use the cat lord's power of [[planes|planar]] travel to journey into the [[Outer Planes]] and, using the [[Claw of Malar]], even challenge [[Tyr]], god of justice, and gain awesome power. In exchange, when he was done with the boy, Duum would give him to the Beastlord. Learning of Duum's wicked intentions for the boy, the Catlord came and rescued him, but Malar pounced upon the Catlord as he fled.{{Cite comic/The Last Betrayal|23}})

The Catlord handed over the boy to the rogue [[Conner]] (who'd been guided onto the scene by the goddess [[Selûne]],{{Cite comic/The Last Betrayal|2}}<ref group="note" name="clawnote">It is unclear how Duum obtained the Claw of Malar, whether from the god Malar himself or separately. The actual details of Duum's and Malar's plan are unknown. However, in the [[1357 DR|Year of the Prince, 1357 DR]], Duum was tricked and thwarted and Tyr seized the Claw of Malar instead.{{Cite comic/The Last Betrayal|14}}

During the [[Time of Troubles]] in [[1358 DR]], Malar's avatar battled [[Sebek]] in the [[Adder Swamp]] in a titanic battle that destroyed large areas of the region.{{Cite polyhedron/108/Forgotten Deities: Sebek|4}}<ref group="note" name="sebeknote">This source states that Malar slew Sebek and assumed control of his cult. However, sourcebooks including ''[[Powers & Pantheons]]'' and ''[[Faiths and Pantheons]]'' directly contradict the claim that Sebek was killed or replaced.

document_data.Relationships:
Malar was one of the [[Deities of Fury]], led by [[Talos]]. He held a long-standing alliance with [[Lolth]] against the [[Seldarine]], and other dark deities like [[Bane]] and [[Loviatar]]. He fought against deities of peace, civilization, and nature, but held particular hate for [[Nobanion]] for defeating him in a battle during the [[Time of Troubles]].
{{Fq
| width  = 250px
| source = Malar refusing to back down.
| text   = I hunt wherever I want and ''whomever'' I want.
}}

After the events of the Spellplague, Malar became subject to Silvanus' rule as a resident of the [[Deep Wilds]]. Despite this, Silvanus did not rein in Malar.{{cite web |url=http://secretsofthearchmages.net/Threads/Wotc/2015/ForgottenRealms/1514971.htm|title=The one and only "Ask the Realms authors/designers thread" 4|accessmonthday=January 29th|accessyear=2017|author=[[Richard Baker]]|date=August 12th, 2008}}

document_data.History:
{{Fq
| width  = 250px
| source = Malar speaking with Lolth.
| text   = It is not my way to humiliate my quarry, but to destroy it. Your ways are not mine, elf, yet I cannot deny the appeal in the picture you paint. A gelded [[Gruumsh]]! I am not a subtle god, but there is irony even I can appreciate!
}}
